.TH "_ctl_verify_adapter" 9 "_ctl_verify_adapter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_ctl_verify_adapter \- validates ioc_number passed from application
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _ctl_verify_adapter
.BI "(int ioc_number "  ","
.BI "struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER **iocpp "  ","
.BI "int mpi_version "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc_number" 12
?
.IP "iocpp" 12
The ioc pointer is returned in this.
.IP "mpi_version" 12
will be MPI2_VERSION for mpt2ctl ioctl device &
MPI25_VERSION | MPI26_VERSION for mpt3ctl ioctl device.
.SH "RETURN"
(-1) means error, else ioc_number.
